{"_id":"JwvWRw0P5XTOWwaf","name":"001 The Primal Vampire Spawn","content":"<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1 id=\"the-primal-vampire-spawn\" style=\"margin-top:0.2em;margin-bottom:0.2em;font-weight:800;font-size:0.987cm;border:0px;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;font-variant-numeric:inherit;font-variant-east-asian:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;line-height:inherit;font-family:MrJeeves;vertical-align:baseline;color:#58180d;column-span:all\">The Primal Vampire Spawn</h1>\n</section>\n<p><img src=\"beneostokens_data/001_vampire_beast/001_vampire_beast-preview.gif\" width=\"673\" height=\"376\" /></p>\n<div style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-variant-numeric:inherit;font-variant-east-asian:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:11.9811px;line-height:inherit;font-family:BookSanity;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-align:justify\">\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.3em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0px 0px 0.8em;z-index:15;break-inside:avoid\">Although they are sadistic tyrants who feast on their victims' desperate screams as greedily as their lifeblood, vampires are able to sustain an aura of nobility. They have some limitations: They may not enter where they are not welcome, cannot cross flowing water and are setablaze under the gaze of the sun. Even their unholy spawn are bound by these shackles. Sometimes a vampire imparts the dubious gift of spawndom upon the wrong soul, stirring primordial horrors from their cursed sleep. These vampire spawns regress to a primal state, becoming a bestial horror of the distant past detached from the rules that even compel their creators, driven only by their lust for terror and agony. Vampires loathe their degenerated and empowered spawn, only those most versed in the lore of the vampiric curse even know about the possibility of creating a Primal Spawn. However, they are not beyond utilizing their cursed creations for personal use.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.3em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin-top:-0.8em;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0px 0px 0.8em;z-index:15;break-inside:avoid;text-indent:1em\">But the Primal Spawns are beyond their unwilling creators' control and they in turn feel disdain for their more ‘evolved’ kin. A Primal Vampire Spawn could be found haunting the deepest dungeons of a Vampire lord's lair, the damp caverns acting as both prison and hunting ground for the deranged creature. They could also act as the uncaring alpha of a pack of lesser Spawns, terrorizing a remote hamlet from a forgotten crypt after the death of their creator. Despite not having a weakness to sunlight, they prefer the shadows, as the darkness supports their preferred hunting style. And if the right opportunity arises, a Primal Vampire Spawn will not hesitate to hunt during broad daylight to indulge in the screams of horrified onlookers.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:1.3em;font-family:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin-top:-0.8em;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0px 0px 0.8em;z-index:15;break-inside:avoid;text-indent:1em\"> </p>\n<h5 id=\"tactics\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-variant-numeric:inherit;font-variant-east-asian:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:0.423cm;line-height:inherit;font-family:ScalySansSmallCaps;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px 0px 0.2em;padding:0px\">Tactics</h5>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-variant-numeric:inherit;font-variant-east-asian:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;line-height:1.5em;font-family:ScalySans;vertical-align:baseline;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0px;z-index:15;break-inside:avoid\">Although the statblock of the Primal Vampire Spawn seems impressive, it would be a waste to just chuck it at the party. It is a creature ripped straight from horror stories told around campfires since the dawn of man, whose blood-curdling screams reverberated from cave walls, as huddled creatures prayed for a sunrise that would not save them. Its ability to walk on walls via <span style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Spider Climb</span> makes it an extremely mobile and versatile hunter that strikes to greatest effect when it gets the drop on its prey. At first it should not try to focus on one player, but rather create an opportunity where vulnerable members of a party can be reached. The combination of <span style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Feeding On Fear</span> and the <span style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Scything Claws</span>’ bleed effect, paired with the combat prowess of the Spawn all but guarantees it’s regenerative ability to kick in with minimal set up.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-variant-numeric:inherit;font-variant-east-asian:inherit;font-stretch:inherit;line-height:1.5em;font-family:ScalySans;vertical-align:baseline;margin-top:-0.8em;margin-bottom:0px;padding:0.8em 0px 0px;z-index:15;break-inside:avoid;text-indent:1em\">The spawn should attack and withdraw before the party gets to mount a coordinated defense - once the Spawn is cornered by close-combat fighters with high AC and hit points, while getting bombarded with spells or arrows from a distance it’s over. It may get some good hits in, but the general oppressive and threatening atmosphere of the encounter will be gone. Both the <span style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Blood-freezing Howl</span> and the <span style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;box-sizing:border-box;border:0px;font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;font-weight:800;font-stretch:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline;margin:0px;padding:0px;letter-spacing:-0.02em\">Bite</span> are handy tools to prevent the players from ganging up on the Spawn. It not only allows the Spawn to remove a party member from combat by paralyzing them, but enables it to abduct a player before retreating back into whatever nightmarish crypt it emerged from. The fight turns into a chase, as the monster uses its superior speed and maneuverability to retreat from a losing fight, having found a victim to feed on. Only when cornered and cut off from possible escape routes, the Spawn will fight to the death and try to brutally maim as many opponents as possible, ending his reign of terror at the apex of a last sanguine bacchanalia.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n<p> </p>","img":"beneostokens_data/001_vampire_beast/001_vampire_beast-idle_face_still.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"aiycoH7UFhTW8VJy":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p5S7Gzmr8NoUUouk"},"exportSource":{"world":"dd5test","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"9.255","systemVersion":"1.5.7"}}}
